24533470.review:
В то время как брэнды жанра "пошаговка с магией и мечами" устраивают пляски на граблях, на сцену выходят новые участники. Thea один из этих новичков, на радость нам, простым игрокам.

Вышло хорошо и годно:
- славянский сеттинг;
- Пантеон, со скиллами, уникальными квестами и разным отношением богов к происходящему на карте;
- множество эвентов, которые можно проходитть разными способами;
- интересные квесты, которые опять-таки можно проходитть разными способами;
- карты генерятся случайно, нет смысла придумывать стандартный шаблон развития, опираясь на какие-то определенные ресурсы, проще и интересней приспосабливатся к каждой частной ситуации; 
- персонажи годные, от характеристик до карточек;
- крафт зависящий от качества материалов и не более;
- застройка поселения;
- возможность изменить сложность игры разными способами в предстартовом меню; 
- текстовая часть;
- звуковая часть;
- БЕСПЛАТНАЯ поддержка разрабов, которые постоянно допиливают игру, вводя новые эвенты, квесты и т.д. 

Может показаться недостаточным: 
- один голос озвучивает все;
- одна деревня и не более;
- играем только людьми (хотя в процессе к нам может присоединится кто угодно, от гоблинов до демонов);
- два главных квеста, плюс квест выбранного божества, плюс всякая рандомно генерящаяся ерунда, все это означает невысокую реиграбельность.

В остатке же неплохая, довольно оригинальная игра, которую вдобавок постепенно улучшают разработчики.

24522903.review:
Review and Tips for Hardcore 
(Tips below are written minimum %230 difficulty )
Review : First of all i must say it is a great game, game dynamics are easy to learn; interface is quite helpful , you can find all  information that you seek, 
All events occur at random, some events may occur more than once and their outcome or following steps may not be the same , you have always there main quest which are cosmic tree, divine  and giants return.  Out of these three quest, first two one is needed to complete game although you may continue to play ;

Tips : (huge map, easy economy, warlord setting, 12 man parties, realistic and paid shuffles etc..)
- Your first building should be a barrack, by this way you wont waste children that are growing tobe soldiers; ( barracks give 10 more skill points, though random this is a nice boost)
- Create all buildings with low quality items to gain their small bonuses ( like carbage attract childeren 2, attract human 1 is more than "0"  :)
- For bees,wasps creature even they are 20 of them make quick combat; it always work but for 3 skeletons minimum you should do manual combat even you are quite strong to finish game;
- in 100 turns you should be able to complete game, to do this a tip , if you be able to survive just with one guy left in party divine quest do it, as your god/goddes will remove all wounds after, 
- Your first expedition should have at least 3-4 gathering tools, this way they dont starve more turns.
- After you have quality items, rebuild buildings;  in the skill points tree the most outern supplies are the most benefit ones to use in a building material , like moonstones, ancient woods, dragon leathers etc..
- For buildings , the primary/secondary item is important and catalizor is not so use normal wood always if you can for buildings; but for items you need a smithy ( a must for later areas) and good catalizor for quality bonuses,
- Unlike other games; crafted items are more powerful then you found in the game; here comes the most important part, your first worker must have a skill of crafting  19 ( more than 19 is useless; and for 19 you need a inventor which comes by its building)  , by this way the crafting item will not a bad quality, even the stats that you see in crafting screen may come more  ( so dont start a crystall abbsy armor with a guy of crafting skill 6 for exp.) , the helpers dont affect what i say here; 
- In later turns , like 200, make another expedition of combined some workers to harvest most critical sources like moonstones, ancient woods etc. (make sure this is also 12 men as well)
- All 12 men parties must have at least 2 piercing weapon , 2 blunt, 1 medic with nice shielding, 2 non-warrior guys for challenges (like ghost, demon,elf, orc etc.) rest are lets say tanks, 
- For fights, most important with order, "first action", "shield ally/support ally "confuse", rest is not quite important, so pay attention to these stats; 
- Save often, especially save when a preferred event happens; by this way even you load that event is there ; 
- For Giants quest, it is possible to choose "fighting" for completing but this is the hard one i must say, as last time i say umbreki giant with 576 health, 196 blunt damage, with 45 leech ; still possible believe me ; cause i always select this for more hard games;
- In some events fighting is not the best option always; for example in an orc event select "work together" then you may receive an orc worker by chance; or orc bandits "ltactics" may give you a orc champion, etc..
- Always carry first 4-6 children with you in expetion, i have no clear proof but they grow in expeditions much more higher rate; and prey your first building barracks to be done before they grow :)
- İn challenges/event the options that are unavaible for that time being is related with races and sometimes with your god. So having all races in your group will show you all options (Like , "Your elf friend knows this sickness, Your dwarf friend can bet with these guys etc.. ) , this is not a must but if you want all options then no racism :)

These are the things i remember; feel free to ask any questions; hope tips will be helpful;

